race.description: Picklebet's Get Your Pickle On Handicap
race.comment: PERFECTLY GOOD (6) raced on the pace from the outset when resuming over 1000m at Albury, beaten 1.4 lengths. Draws well and will present fitter for the longer sprint. Rates tough to beat. QUICK SPELL (13) is going well and the Maiden win at Wagga Riverside was good. McDougall is reunited and that's a decent push for his chance. Draws to advantage. LOVEOFMYLIFE (10) has had one blip in a string of solid efforts. This is a little harder, but she has plenty of weight relief, and the blinkers go on for the first time. Keep safe. BRON (11) has the rail and 3kg claim and brings a Maiden win from Berrigan. Tougher, but she's lightly raced with scope for more improvement. MISS LOTTIE (8) has placed 2/3 second-up and will improve.
